<h2 id="titles-meta">1. Titles & Meta Descriptions</h2>
<ul>
<li>Use primary keywords in <strong>page title</strong> and <strong>meta description</strong></li>
<li>Keep titles <strong>50–60 characters</strong> and meta descriptions <strong>150–160 characters</strong></li>
<li>Include local keywords: e.g., <em>"SEO services Nairobi, Kenya"</em></li>
<li>Make meta descriptions compelling to boost click-through rates (CTR)</li>
</ul>
<p>Internal link: <a href="/blog/why-website-not-ranking-google-2026.html">Why Your Website Isn’t Ranking</a></p>

<h2 id="headings">2. Headings Structure (H1-H6)</h2>
<ul>
<li>Each page should have only one H1</li>
<li>Use H2 and H3 to organize content logically</li>
<li>Include keywords naturally in headings</li>
<li>Make headings user-friendly and descriptive</li>
</ul>

<h2 id="content">3. Content Optimization</h2>
<ul>
<li>Create original, helpful, and high-quality content</li>
<li>Use bullet points, short paragraphs, and subheadings</li>
<li>Include local references and examples for Kenya</li>
<li>Regularly update content to keep it relevant</li>
</ul>
<p>Internal link: <a href="/blog/local-seo-small-business-nairobi.html">Local SEO Guide for Small Businesses</a></p>

<h2 id="keywords">4. Keyword Usage & Density</h2>
<ul>
<li>Include primary keywords naturally within the first 100 words</li>
<li>Use long-tail keywords for targeted search traffic</li>
<li>Do not keyword stuff; maintain natural flow</li>
<li>Use LSI keywords and synonyms for semantic SEO</li>
</ul>

<h2 id="images">5. Images & Alt Text</h2>
<ul>
<li>Compress images to improve page speed</li>
<li>Add descriptive alt text with target keywords</li>
<li>Use WebP format for faster loading</li>
<li>Include captions if necessary to explain images</li>
</ul>

<h2 id="links">6. Internal & External Linking</h2>
<ul>
<li>Link to relevant pages on your website</li>
<li>Use descriptive anchor text for internal links</li>
<li>Link to authoritative external sources where needed</li>
<li>Check for broken links regularly</li>
</ul>
<p>Internal links:  
<a href="/blog/technical-seo-explained-2026.html">Technical SEO Guide</a>,  
<a href="/blog/shopify-seo-guide-beginners-2026.html">Shopify SEO Guide</a></p>

<h2 id="url">7. SEO-Friendly URLs</h2>
<ul>
<li>Use short, descriptive URLs with keywords</li>
<li>Separate words with hyphens, not underscores</li>
<li>Avoid dynamic parameters where possible</li>
<li>Maintain consistency across the website</li>
</ul>

<h2 id="mobile">8. Mobile Optimization</h2>
<ul>
<li>Ensure your website is fully responsive</li>
<li>Text should be readable without zooming</li>
<li>Buttons and links should be easily clickable</li>
<li>Check mobile page speed</li>
</ul>

<h2 id="speed">9. Page Speed & Core Web Vitals</h2>
<ul>
<li>LCP under 2.5s, FID under 100ms, CLS under 0.1</li>
<li>Enable browser caching & compression</li>
<li>Minimize render-blocking JavaScript & CSS</li>
<li>Use a fast hosting provider</li>
</ul>
<p>Internal link: <a href="/blog/website-traffic-growth-seo-kenya/">Website Traffic Growth SEO Guide</a></p>

<h2 id="schema">10. Structured Data & Schema</h2>
<ul>
<li>Add schema for articles, products, FAQs, and reviews</li>
<li>Helps Google display rich snippets in SERPs</li>
<li>Improves click-through rates</li>
</ul>

<h2 id="social">11. Social Sharing & Open Graph</h2>
<ul>
<li>Optimize Open Graph tags for Facebook and LinkedIn</li>
<li>Use Twitter Cards for Twitter sharing</li>
<li>Ensure images, titles, and descriptions appear correctly</li>
</ul>

<h2 id="analytics">12. Analytics & Monitoring</h2>
<ul>
<li>Track user behavior via Google Analytics</li>
<li>Monitor indexing and rankings in Google Search Console</li>
<li>Regularly audit pages with SEO tools (Ahrefs, SEMrush)</li>
</ul>

